$MSFT & $ATVI - There is a potential $19.00 arbitrage opportunity, regarding this merger. According the Barron's there is a 60% chance the buyout will happen, and people holding shares of $ATVI should profit. However, capital hill could stop the deal (anti-trust). Result, $ATVI falls back down to it's original levels, leaving shareholders bagholding. How does one avoid this? You would need to make sure your stop loss is on in the pre-market and after hours market every day (before and after the bell). Could something happen, Merger fail press release on a Saturday, the stock then falls, and your broker screws you Monday morning bag holding: absolutely.
